3. When the skin starts to split at the top of the tomato, pull the tomato out and put it into a bowl of ice water. This step is correct, as it helps stop the cooking process and makes the skin easier to peel.
4. Use your hands to peel the skin off. This step is correct, as it allows for easy removal of the skin.

