final_output_text: To determine whether to wear the wedding ring on the right or left hand, we need to consider the anatomy of the human hand and the typical placement of the ring finger.

1. The ring finger is the fourth finger on the hand, and it is located on the opposite side of the thumb from the pinky finger.
2. In most people, the ring finger is on the left side of the hand when the thumb is on the right side.
3. Therefore, the ring finger is typically on the left side of the hand, which corresponds to the left hand.
4. This is why, in most cultures, it is customary to wear the wedding ring on the left ring finger of the left hand.

