final_output_text: To protect a garden from ice frost, we need to consider the effectiveness of each solution in retaining heat and preventing damage to the plants. 

Solution 0: Place bed sheet on soil.
This method involves laying a bed sheet directly on the soil. The sheet acts as an insulator, trapping the heat from the soil and preventing it from escaping into the cold air. This can help to keep the soil warm and protect the roots of the plants from freezing temperatures. However, this method may not be as effective as other solutions, as the sheet may not cover the entire garden area and could be easily disturbed by wind or other external factors.

Solution 1: Place bed sheet over garden.
This method involves laying a bed sheet over the entire garden area. The sheet acts as a barrier, preventing cold air from reaching the plants and keeping the heat from the soil trapped. This method is more effective than Solution 0, as it covers the entire garden area and provides better insulation. Additionally, it is easier to maintain and less likely to be disturbed by external factors.

Considering the effectiveness and ease of maintenance, Solution 1 is the better option for protecting a garden from ice frost.

The answer is 1.

